t and what little investigation was done was woeful, inconsistent and avoided responding to the issues.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> I complained to t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he Local Government Ombudsman. She</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> decided that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he would not i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">nvestigate as I had not suffered any injustice. In coming to this conclusion the Ombudsman decided that:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:16pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; orphans:0; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Although my garden adjoined the caravan park, my home was at the other end of the garden and there were some trees screening the caravan park.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:16pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; orphans:0; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">There wa</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s a road that took traffic away from the site </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to the north </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and therefore the traffic did not have to go past my home.</span></li></ul><p style="line-height:16pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:16pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Ombudsman made it clear that although the caravan park joined my property, because my house was some 70m away at the other end of the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> garden, there was no detrimen